{
  "attrs": {
    "abstract": "The ESA Fire Disturbance Climate Change Initiative (Fire_cci) project has produced maps of global burned area developed from satellite observations. The Small Fire Database (SFD) pixel products have been obtained by combining spectral information from Sentinel-2 MSI data and thermal information from VIIRS VNP14IMGML active fire products.\n\nThis gridded dataset has been derived from the Small Fire Database (SFD) Burned Area pixel product for Sub-Saharan Africa, v2.0 (also available), which covers Sub-Saharan Africa for the year 2019, by summarising its burned area information into a regular grid covering the Earth at 0.05 x 0.05 degrees resolution and at monthly temporal resolution.",
    "catalog_url": "https://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/01b00854797d44a59d57c8cce08821eb",
    "cci_project": "FIRE",
    "comment": "These data were produced as part of the ESA CCI programme.",
